{2000}{}{Hello, traveler. Welcome to Vault City. Is there anything I can help you with?}
{2010}{}{Who are you?}
{2020}{}{What is this place?}
{2030}{}{Nothing today, thanks.}
{3000}{}{Name's Wallace. I'm the Customs Officer for Vault City. I accommodate those who wish to conduct business within our great walls.}
{3010}{}{The information I possess is really important. Really.}
{3020}{}{I see. Thanks for the information}
{4000}{}{If you want to enter Vault City, then you'll need a good reason. Only a Vault Citizen has the right to come and go as they please. All others must procure a Day Pass.}
{4010}{}{I'd like to enter the city.}
{4020}{}{What's a Day Pass?}
{4030}{}{I see. Thanks for the information.}
{5000}{}{This is the Customs Office for Vault City. We're responsible for keeping a log of all the goods that come to us via the caravans and supervising all transactions. All merchants must pass through customs before entering the city.}
{5010}{}{I'd like to enter the city.}
{5020}{}{What goods do you receive from the caravans?}
{5030}{}{I see. Thanks for the information.}
{6000}{}{Depends on where the caravan is from. We get shipments from many places... Servants from the Den, uranium from Broken Hills, and metal ore from Redding.}
{6010}{}{What can you tell me about the Den?}
{6020}{}{What can you tell me about Broken Hills?}
{6030}{}{What can you tell me about Redding?}
{6040}{}{Can I ask you another question?}
{6050}{}{I see. Thanks for the information.}
{7000}{}{Those who need to deal directly with the merchants or the First Citizen are given a Day Pass. Only those with Day Passes can enter the city.}
{7010}{}{Can I ask you some other questions?}
{7020}{}{Thanks for the information. Goodbye.}
